ot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Offensive Social Media Post\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?fit=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?fit=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-781\" src=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?resize=238%2C333&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"238\" height=\"333\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?w=1000&amp;ssl=1 1000w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?resize=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1 214w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?resize=768%2C1075&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?resize=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 731w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 238px) 100vw, 238px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I really dislike cards that completely void a particular strategy, which is why I was surprised by how well Offensive Social Media post does so. Also- and I am not kidding about this- Offensive Social Media Post has negated the effect of Letting Others Copy three separate times! This change clarifies that players can still gain friends from Teacher Abilities, club effects and event cards. That doesn&#8217;t sound like a big difference, but it really can be as it makes gaining Friends much more difficult, but still possible.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Were these changes fair? Let me know what you think in the comments below!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Hey everyone! Today we will be discussing a few of the changes with the Sophomore deck. Sophomore year was designed to be reflective of sophomore year at my school: more difficult classes and less support. Even though the Sophomore deck has a lot more total action points than the Freshman deck, a large portion of &#8230; <a title=\"Sophomore deck changes\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/08\/sophomore-deck-changes\/\" aria-label=\"More on Sophomore deck changes\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":781,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"spay_email":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?fit=1000%2C1400&ssl=1","jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":592,"url":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/adjusting-cards-part-two\/","url_meta":{"origin":776,"position":0},"title":"Adjusting Cards (part two)","date":"July 27, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Hello everyone! Today I thought I would write a bit about the adjustments I have made recently to the Sophomore deck. These mainly consist of small action point buffs to make Sophomore year a lot less difficult. There is some history to a very difficult Sophomore year: at my high\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Daggers High&quot;","img":{"alt_text":"","src":"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Final-Exams-1.png?fit=857%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200","width":350,"height":200},"classes":[]},{"id":895,"url":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/09\/play-testing\/","url_meta":{"origin":776,"position":1},"title":"Mega Post! Photos, Balance Changes, and New Rulebook","date":"September 14, 2018","format":false,"exce